# Sidekick — persistent restartable Claude Code teammate

> **DRAFT — proposed rewrite.** Not deployed. Original lives at
> `~/.claude/skills/sidekick/SKILL.md`. Diff vs original is summarized at the
> bottom of this file. To activate, run `/advice` on this draft, address all
> CONFIRMED findings, then `mv` over the original.

One named background teammate owns long-running orchestration. The main session
supervises and relays milestones. If the conversation crashes, a fresh session
respawns the sidekick and it resumes from a disk state file with zero
conversation context.

## Hard pre-flight gates (REQUIRED before any teammate or tmux path)

**These are HARD gates. If any of these fail, DO NOT silently fall back to a
different execution path. Surface the failure to the user.**

1. **`CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` must be exported in the spawning shell.** Verified
   with `[[ -n "$CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR" ]] && [[ -d "$CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR" ]]`.
   Failure mode (2026-07-11): `${CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR:-$HOME/.claude}` silently
   fell back to the default account, which has no auth for the WA user →
   "Not logged in · Please run /login" exit=1. Skill doc previously implied
   inline propagation was sufficient; the inline form `${CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR:-...}`
   only works if the variable is exported, which Claude Code's bash shell does
   NOT do by default.

2. **Auth reachability check.** Before any teammate spawn, verify the account
   reachable via `claude -p "echo SIDEKICK_AUTH_OK"` (≤5s). If it fails,
   surface the failure and DO NOT proceed.

3. **`isActive:true` ack required within 30s of registration**
   *(isActive is an internal field observed in
   `~/.claude*/teams/session-*/config.json` — undocumented, may change
   without notice; the 30s threshold is a local convention from 2026-07-11
   repro timings — not an Anthropic SLA)*. A teammate is registered when
   its entry appears in `~/.claude/teams/<session>/config.json`. It is
   **NOT** ready for work until `isActive` flips to `true` AND its inbox
   is non-empty. Failure mode (2026-07-11, anthropics/claude-code#24108
   — closed as duplicate, verified 2026-07-11 via `gh api`): teammate
   registered with the mission in `prompt:` field but never read its
   mailbox — `isActive: false` indefinitely, survived 3 SendMessage
   nudges and 4 `idle_notification`s, produced zero output for 5+
   minutes. **If `isActive` does not flip within 30 seconds
   *(local convention from 2026-07-11 repro timings — not an Anthropic
   SLA)*, surface the hang to the user with a clear remediation and DO
   NOT silently fall back to tmux.**

4. **TUI visual lanes require matching on-disk registry.** If the TUI bottom
   bar shows `◯ <lane-name>` but `~/.claude/teams/<session>/config.json` does
   NOT list `<lane-name>` as a member, the lane is a phantom. Failure mode
   (2026-07-11, anthropics/claude-code#24771 — closed as duplicate, verified
   2026-07-11 via `gh api`): sidekick spawned 4+ minutes of forensic search
   for a teammate that doesn't exist in any registry. **A phantom lane is
   unrecoverable for this session — disclose to user and recommend `/advice`
   for diagnosis.**

## DEFAULT MODE: in-session teammate (user directive 2026-07-11)

Per claude-code CHANGELOG v2.1.178: "every session now has one implicit
team — spawn teammates directly with the Agent tool's name parameter".
Spawn the sidekick (and its lanes) as named teammates of the
INVOKING session's implicit Agent Team via the `Agent` tool with
`{name, model: "sonnet", run_in_background: true}`. This is what "real
`/team-claude`" means — the roster is visible in the user's own panel,
every member is SendMessage-addressable both ways, and the user can
watch/steer without attaching to anything.

- Durability = **STATE.md checkpoints + a P1 resumption bead (`br`) +
  commit-often**, NOT process persistence. Teammates die with the
  conversation; that is an accepted trade for visibility. On crash: a
  fresh session re-reads STATE.md / `br show <runbook-bead>` and respawns
  the same named teammates.
- **External `tmux new-session` sidekicks are the FALLBACK ONLY** — for
  missions that must survive the conversation process itself (multi-day
  unattended runs) or when Agent Teams is unavailable. When used:
  - Pre-flight gate #1 must pass
  - The user must be told explicitly that the sidekick will NOT appear
    in their panel
  - Provide the exact attach command (`tmux attach -t <session>`)
  - Prefer INTERACTIVE (TUI) over `-p` for any tmux spawn the user may
    want to watch

**Everything below (tmux launch commands, engines, stall watchdog) applies to
the FALLBACK external-tmux mode. The STATE.md / beads / commit-often /
milestone-reporting protocol applies to BOTH modes.**

The known failure modes of the tmux path are documented below in "Known bug
class" — read them before choosing tmux as the fallback.

## Invocation

`/sidekick [sonnet|codex] [mission...]`

- `engine/model`: default is **claude with Sonnet**. `codex` selects the Codex
  CLI engine (below). Any other model only if the user explicitly asks in
  the current message.
- `mission`: freeform priorities. If omitted, resume whatever the state file says.

## Engines: claude (default) | codex — both verified 2026-07-10

The protocol (STATE.md, tmux, commit-often, respawn) is engine-agnostic. Only
the launch command and the between-run steering command differ.

**codex launch** (auth comes from `~/.codex` — no `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` needed):

```bash
tmux new-session -d -s "$SESSION" -x 160 -y 48 \
  "cd '$PWD' && codex exec --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox --skip-git-repo-check \"\$(cat '$STATE_DIR/sidekick.prompt.md')\"; rc=\$?; printf '\n[sidekick done exit=%s]\n' \"\$rc\"; exec bash"
```

Verify with `pgrep -fl "codex exec"`; unlike claude `-p`, codex exec streams
progress into the pane while working.

**Mode choice: `-p` (headless) vs interactive TUI — verified 2026-07-10.**
`-p` is the default for unattended batch missions (clean `[sidekick done
exit=]` marker), but it gets NO team primitives. For missions that benefit
from a REAL in-sidekick Claude team or live steering, launch the interactive
TUI in tmux instead:

```bash
# MANDATORY: export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR FIRST
export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR="$HOME/.claude-wa"   # or your account dir; MUST be exported
tmux new-session -d -s "$SESSION" -x 200 -y 50 \
  "cd '$PWD' && CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR='$CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR' CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1 claude --model sonnet --teammate-mode tmux --dangerously-skip-permissions; exec bash"
```

**Pre-flight gate #1 check**: `[[ -n "$CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR" ]]` MUST be true
before running this command. If false, ABORT — do not run the tmux launch.

- First run in a new directory shows a **trust dialog** — capture-pane, then
  `tmux send-keys -t "$SESSION" Enter` to accept before sending the mission.
- Deliver the mission as a pointer to STATE.md (single source of truth), with
  text and the submitting Enter as **separate** send-keys calls.
- **Completion detection** (no exit marker in TUI mode): gate on the
  STATE.md condition, not the pane alone.
- **Teardown** (the TUI never exits on its own):
  `tmux kill-session -t "$SESSION"` after verifying STATE.md shows
  "(mission complete)" and deliverables are on disk.

## Known bug class (the model cannot fix these)

The five bugs below were reproduced live on 2026-07-11 and explain every
silent failure observed in today's diagnostic. They are upstream of this
skill — the model can detect them but cannot patch them. When you see the
symptom, surface it; do not silently work around. **All four Anthropic
issues are now closed upstream (verified 2026-07-11 via `gh api`):
#24108 closed/duplicate, #24771 closed/duplicate, #46691 closed/not_planned,
#24292 closed/duplicate.** Reproduction still happens locally because the
upstream fixes have not yet landed in the installed `claude` binary.

| Issue | Status (verified 2026-07-11 via `gh api`) | Symptom | Reproduced 2026-07-11 |
|---|---|---|---|
| [anthropics/claude-code#24108](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24108) | closed as duplicate | Teammate stuck at idle prompt; mailbox never polled; no `--prompt` flag passed. In-process probe registered with mission in `prompt:` field but `isActive: false` indefinitely, 3 SendMessage nudges ignored, 4 `idle_notification`s, zero output for 5+ min. | ✅ |
| [anthropics/claude-code#46691](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/46691) | closed not_planned | Lead stalls after teammates report back; needs keystroke to unblock. TUI sidekick stalled 4+ min searching for phantom lane; SendMessage nudges queued; only unblocked when tmux send-keys delivered keystroke. | ✅ |
| [anthropics/claude-code#24771](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24771) | closed as duplicate | Teammate pane creation works but routing to pane broken. TUI showed `◯ lane-test-1` in bottom bar but `~/.claude/teams/<session>/config.json` only had `team-lead`. | ✅ |
| [anthropics/claude-code#24292](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24292) | closed as duplicate | tmux silent fallback to in-process. First `-p` tmux sidekick failed with "Not logged in" because `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` was unset and bashrc parameter expansion fell back to default account. | ✅ |
| [anthropics/claude-code#23513](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/23513) | closed not_planned | tmux send-keys race with shell init. Some SendMessage nudges never landed. | plausible |

When the symptom matches, the right action is to:
1. Document the failure with timestamps + file:line evidence
2. Recommend the user file/track the issue
3. If the failure is recoverable, retry with the documented workaround
4. If not recoverable for this session, disclose and recommend `/advice`

Do NOT silently fall back to an alternative execution path — that hides the
bug and erodes user trust.

